## Freeze Panes Setup

**Freeze Settings:**
- **Freeze:** Row 1 (header stays visible when scrolling down)
- **Optional:** Also freeze Column A for row labels (View → Freeze → 1 column)

**In Google Sheets:**
1. Click on Row 2, Column A (cell A2)
2. Go to View → Freeze → 1 row
3. Optional: Click on Row 1, Column B → View → Freeze → 1 row and 1 column

---

## Print Layout (if printing)

**Page Setup:**
- **Orientation:** Landscape
- **Paper:** Letter (8.5" × 11")
- **Margins:** 0.5" all sides
- **Scale:** 1 page wide × 2 pages tall (adjust to fit)
- **Include:** Headers (print row 1-3)

---

## Responsive Design Tips

For mobile or narrow views:
- Dashboard is best viewed on desktop (wide screens)
- Use View → Freeze panes to keep headers visible
- Consider using filters on large tables
- Charts may stack or resize — acceptable for monitoring

---

## Accessibility

- Use sufficient color contrast (all text readable)
- Don't rely solely on color for meaning (use text labels too)
- Use clear, descriptive headers
- Avoid flashing or animation

---

## Dark Mode Compatibility

Google Sheets supports dark mode. Test your dashboard:
- Light colors remain readable
- Borders still visible
- Tables stay clear

**If needed, adjust:**
- Header background to darker shade (test in dark mode)
- KPI card background to slightly darker light blue

---

## Before Sharing

**Checklist:**
- ✅ All formulas working (no #ERROR or #VALUE! errors)
- ✅ Charts updated with test data
- ✅ Conditional formatting applied
- ✅ Column widths adjusted for readability
- ✅ Last Updated timestamp shows current date/time
- ✅ All sections have descriptive headers
- ✅ Borders and spacing consistent
- ✅ No personal or sensitive test data visible
- ✅ Share settings appropriate (view/edit as needed)

---

## Monthly Maintenance

Every month:
1. Verify all date formulas (THIS Month vs last month)
2. Check that recent data flows into Recent Leads section
3. Review conditional formatting highlighting (ensure still accurate)
4. Archive old leads if data grows very large
5. Verify charts are pulling latest data

